                </a></li></ul></div><p><strong>Figure 2.  <span>Difference in QFT results (test–re-test) versus the average of QFT test and re-test results (all on the log scale).</span></strong></p><a id="article1.body1.sec3.sec2.fig2.caption1.p1" name="article1.body1.sec3.sec2.fig2.caption1.p1"></a><p>Separate plotting characters are used for each individual and the mean log-difference is shown as the broken horizontal line. We note that there tend to be more points above zero and hence the average difference (test–re-test) lies above 0, indicating higher IFN-γ results upon re-testing of the same specimens. QFT: QuantiFERON-TB Gold In Tube®; IFN-γ: interferon-gamma.</p>
